reviewText: Hilarious Canadian sit-com.
Hilarious!! Purchased as a gift for my husband (he loved it); then became a fan of the show myself after watching!! Great find on this one!!

The only bad thing about this show is they stopped making them. I felt kind of like Mr Lahey, "What would I do without my Randy?". Well, by some miracle they are again, and I was so impressed. The cast is doing what they do best, making me laugh my butt off!
It's great!
Proof that the boys have what it takes even without the brilliant mind of their former director to quench the thirst of a seasoned tpb fan.
These guys a so funny!!!

I really miss watching TPB on TV.  I did subscribe to swearnet but stopped watching it because most of the content was behind the scenes footage and touring footage, rather than new comedy.  Also I bought Don't Legalize it and didn't really like it. This set feels a lot like the good old days.  I've just watched the 4th episode.

Looks like this time they filmed in another different trailer park.  I am glad to see most of the gang back. I wish that Trevor was back too but I understand that he and Corey were treated badly by Clattenberg, etc.  I am glad that Ray is no longer hogging the air time.  RIP Phil Collins.  I think I recognize Donald/Dawn from an earlier episode ("enchantee").

I hope they make season 9 and keep going.

PS I wanted to add that there is only one thing I hated in Season 8: Bubbles using puppets AGAIN.
Got this on pre-order from Amazon.ca great season.  And if you haven't subscribed to swearnet your seriously missing out

10 episodes that fly by. I didn't know what to expect since the original show's demise, but these guys have far surpassed the original. I think I even saw Trevor under the red hat at the hardware store. All the favorite characters are back, Cory, Sam Losco, Cyrus, Sebastian Bach,  George Green, Jacob, J ROC and T, the ROC Pile and even Steve Rodgers. A great story line, a funny new character with Don/Donna, and poor little Orangie and Talk-O. I think this was their best season ever, and I have their entire collection of movies, specials and the original series. Buy it, you won't regret it.
